{
  "info": {
    "name": "Expense Splitter API",
    "description": "Backend API for the Expense Splitter (Go + Echo + Postgres + Keycloak).\n\n## Quick start\n1. Bring the stack up: `docker compose up --build -d` (server on http://localhost:8080).\n2. Run **Auth → Login** — it stores the Keycloak access token into the `access_token` collection variable; every authed request inherits it via collection-level Bearer auth.\n3. Run **Groups → Create group** — stores `groupId` (and `inviteToken`).\n4. Run **Account → Get me** — stores your `userId`.\n5. Record/list expenses, manage members, etc.\n\n## Parameters\n- **Path variables** (`:groupId`, `:userId`, `:expenseId`) appear in each request's **Params** tab and are pre-filled from the collection variables below (set automatically by the test scripts). Override them per-request there.\n- **Query params** (list expenses: `category`, `paid_by`, `q`) also live in the Params tab — enable the checkbox to apply a filter.\n- **Body** params are in the Body tab (raw JSON).\n\n## Variables (collection → Variables tab)\n- `baseUrl` (default http://localhost:8080)\n- `email` / `password` — login creds (default: seed global admin admin@expense-splitter.local / admin)\n- `newUserEmail` / `newUserPassword` / `newUserName` — used by Auth → Register\n- `groupId`, `userId`, `expenseId`, `inviteToken` — auto-filled by test scripts, or set manually.\n\nNote: login is proxied through our API (`/auth/login`), so you only ever hit `{{baseUrl}}`, never Keycloak directly.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8080" },
    { "key": "email", "value": "admin@expense-splitter.local" },
    { "key": "password", "value": "admin" },
    { "key": "newUserEmail", "value": "testuser@example.com" },
    { "key": "newUserPassword", "value": "password123" },
    { "key": "newUserName", "value": "Test User" },
    { "key": "access_token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "groupId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "userId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "memberUserId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "expenseId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "inviteToken", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health check",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Public liveness/DB-ping check."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth (public)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register (sign up)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (j && j.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('memberUserId', j.id); console.log('memberUserId stored: ' + j.id); }",
                  "pm.test('status is 201 or 409', () => pm.expect([201,409]).to.include(pm.response.code));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{newUserEmail}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{newUserPassword}}\",\n  \"name\": \"{{newUserName}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Creates the user in Keycloak (admin API) and provisions the local users row. Body: email, password (>= 8 chars), name."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (j && j.access_token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', j.access_token);",
                  "  console.log('access_token stored');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('has access_token', () => pm.expect(j.access_token).to.be.a('string'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Password-grant login proxied to Keycloak. On success stores {{access_token}} for all other requests."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Account",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get me",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (j && j.local_user && j.local_user.id) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', j.local_user.id);",
                  "  console.log('userId stored: ' + j.local_user.id);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/me",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["me"]
            },
            "description": "Returns token claims + the linked local user (if provisioned). Stores {{userId}}."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Register (link existing token)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/register",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["register"]
            },
            "description": "Provision-or-link the authenticated Keycloak identity to a local users row (idempotent). Used e.g. by the seeded admin on first login."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Submit verification",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/verification",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["verification"]
            },
            "description": "Moves the caller from registered -> pending_verification."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Groups",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List my groups",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups"]
            },
            "description": "Groups the caller belongs to (approved memberships) with their role/status."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create group (as verified user)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (j && j.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('groupId', j.id); console.log('groupId stored: ' + j.id); }",
                  "if (j && j.invite_token) { pm.collectionVariables.set('inviteToken', j.invite_token); }",
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Road Trip 2026\",\n  \"start_date\": \"2026-07-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"end_date\": \"2026-07-10T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"expected_member_count\": 4\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups"]
            },
            "description": "Use this when logged in as a NORMAL verified user — the creator becomes group-admin. Do NOT send admin_user_id here (a non-admin sending it gets 403). Stores {{groupId}} and {{inviteToken}}. Dates are RFC3339 timestamps.\n\nNote: the seed admin is the GLOBAL admin and cannot use this form — use \"Create group (as global admin — assign member)\" instead."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create group (as global admin — assign member)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (j && j.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('groupId', j.id); console.log('groupId stored: ' + j.id); }",
                  "if (j && j.invite_token) { pm.collectionVariables.set('inviteToken', j.invite_token); }",
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Admin-Assigned Trip\",\n  \"start_date\": \"2026-07-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"end_date\": \"2026-07-10T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"admin_user_id\": \"{{memberUserId}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups"]
            },
            "description": "Use this when logged in as the GLOBAL admin. You must assign an existing VERIFIED member as group-admin via admin_user_id (the global admin is not a trip member). {{userId}} is captured by Auth → Register / Get me — verify that user first (Admin → Approve user). Stores {{groupId}} and {{inviteToken}}."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get group (details + members)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups/:groupId",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups", ":groupId"],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "groupId", "value": "{{groupId}}", "description": "Group UUID" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Group metadata + member list. Member-level access."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update group",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Road Trip 2026 (renamed)\",\n  \"start_date\": \"2026-07-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"end_date\": \"2026-07-12T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"expected_member_count\": 5\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups/:groupId",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups", ":groupId"],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "groupId", "value": "{{groupId}}", "description": "Group UUID" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Replace editable metadata. Group-admin only, open groups only."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Close group (compute settlement)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups/:groupId/close",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups", ":groupId", "close"],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "groupId", "value": "{{groupId}}", "description": "Group UUID" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Group-admin closes the group -> freezes expenses and computes the settlement plan (payments)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Memberships",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Join group (request)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"invite_token\": \"{{inviteToken}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups/join",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups", "join"]
            },
            "description": "Verified user requests to join using the group's shareable invite token."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List join requests",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const arr = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (Array.isArray(arr) && arr.length && arr[0].user_id) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('memberUserId', arr[0].user_id);",
                  "  console.log('memberUserId stored (first requester): ' + arr[0].user_id);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups/:groupId/requests",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups", ":groupId", "requests"],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "groupId", "value": "{{groupId}}", "description": "Group UUID" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Group-admin view of pending join requests."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Approve member",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups/:groupId/members/:userId/approve",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups", ":groupId", "members", ":userId", "approve"],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "groupId", "value": "{{groupId}}", "description": "Group UUID" },
                { "key": "userId", "value": "{{memberUserId}}", "description": "Target user UUID" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Group-admin approves a join request."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Reject member",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups/:groupId/members/:userId/reject",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups", ":groupId", "members", ":userId", "reject"],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "groupId", "value": "{{groupId}}", "description": "Group UUID" },
                { "key": "userId", "value": "{{memberUserId}}", "description": "Target user UUID" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Group-admin rejects a join request."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Promote to admin (handoff)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups/:groupId/members/:userId/promote",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups", ":groupId", "members", ":userId", "promote"],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "groupId", "value": "{{groupId}}", "description": "Group UUID" },
                { "key": "userId", "value": "{{memberUserId}}", "description": "New admin's user UUID" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Transfer group-admin role to another approved member (exactly one admin at all times)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Remove member",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups/:groupId/members/:userId",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups", ":groupId", "members", ":userId"],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "groupId", "value": "{{groupId}}", "description": "Group UUID" },
                { "key": "userId", "value": "{{memberUserId}}", "description": "Target user UUID" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Remove a member (or leave). Blocked (409) if the member has any recorded expense."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Expenses",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Record expense",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (j && j.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('expenseId', j.id); console.log('expenseId stored: ' + j.id); }",
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"amount_baisa\": 15000,\n  \"category\": \"food\",\n  \"description\": \"dinner at the hardware store cafe\",\n  \"occurred_on\": \"2026-07-03\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups/:groupId/expenses",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups", ":groupId", "expenses"],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "groupId", "value": "{{groupId}}", "description": "Group UUID" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Record an expense you paid. paid_by is always the caller. category in: lodging, fuel, food, transport, other. occurred_on is YYYY-MM-DD within the trip range. Stores {{expenseId}}."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List expenses (with filters)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups/:groupId/expenses?category=food&paid_by={{userId}}&q=dinner",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups", ":groupId", "expenses"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "category", "value": "food", "description": "lodging|fuel|food|transport|other", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "paid_by", "value": "{{userId}}", "description": "Filter by payer user UUID", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "q", "value": "dinner", "description": "Search in description", "disabled": true }
              ],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "groupId", "value": "{{groupId}}", "description": "Group UUID" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "List expenses for a group. Descriptions >80 chars are truncated on a word boundary. Optional query filters (enable them in the Params tab): category, paid_by (user id), q (description search)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update expense",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"amount_baisa\": 18000,\n  \"category\": \"food\",\n  \"description\": \"dinner at the hardware store cafe (updated)\",\n  \"occurred_on\": \"2026-07-03\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/groups/:groupId/expenses/:expenseId",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["groups", ":groupId", "expenses", ":expenseId"],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "groupId", "value": "{{groupId}}", "description": "Group UUID" },
                { "key": "expenseId", "value": "{{expenseId}}", "description": "Expense UUID" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Edit your own expense while the group is open. An amount change is written to the audit log (before/after)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Admin (global admin)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Approve user (verify)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/users/:userId/approve",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "users", ":userId", "approve"],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "userId", "value": "{{memberUserId}}", "description": "Target user UUID to verify" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Global admin marks a user verified. Requires the caller to be the global admin."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Reject user",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/users/:userId/reject",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "users", ":userId", "reject"],
              "variable": [
                { "key": "userId", "value": "{{memberUserId}}", "description": "Target user UUID to reject" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Global admin rejects a user's verification. Requires the caller to be the global admin."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
